While the negative control plates remained sterile, stool specimens grew Candida albicans (4 positive), Trichosporon asahii (4 positive), Malassezia restricta (2 positive), and Candida glabrata, Clavispora lusitaniae, Debaryomyces hansenii, Malassezia sp., Corticiaceae sp., Davidiella tassiana, Davidiella sp., and Penicillium sp. each in one specimen. The four later fungal species were detected uniquely by culture-dependant methods (
